The paper deals with a communication problem in which a large number of users transmit data to a base station without coordination, which is a typical problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed solution leverages the spatial dimensionality of large-scale antenna arrays, which is a key feature of massive MIMO (cs.MM). The paper also uses compressive sensing techniques, which are relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
